 of flood control, open space design and ecology at the same time, often a challenging task for the designer. This book is the product of extensive research that identified some 60 best-practice examples and subjected them to a comparative analysis. The result is a systematic catalog of effective strategies and innovative design tools that provides readers with an inspiring overview of the broad spectrum of design possibilities for river spaces. Each project is illustrated with photographs taken especially for the book and each design strategy and tool is explained by diagrams.This revised edition introduces ten new case studies chiefly from North America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCity planning. 0aLandscape architecture. 0aWater and architecture. 0aWaterfronts. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh1 aBajc, Katarina, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDreiseitl, Herbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStimberg, Daniel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aStokman, Antje, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVoermanek, Hinnerk, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aZeller, Susanne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2017z9783110547719oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z97831106252640 cprintz978303561186140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303561042040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035610